# Ontology Diff Report

 * neuro
   * Fixing isa->partof for parts of fornix . See [1277](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1277)
   * remove subthalamic fasciculus po VT. See [1277](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1277)
   * splitting limen of insula, [1279](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1279)
 * developmental
   * Making presumptive paraxial mesoderm part-of blastula. See [1277](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1277)
   * NT: cardiopharyngeal field, fixes [1263](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1263)
   * primary heart field part of cardiopharyngeal field, fixes [1263](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1263)
 * evolutionary
   * Added various subtypes of placenta, and added taxon constraints
   * NT: orovelar muscle. Fixes [1264](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1264)
   * NT: oral siphon muscle. Fixes [1265](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1265)
   * Taxon constraints for nose
 * Other
   * generalizing pancreatic duct. Fixes [1250](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1250)
   * NT: for skin appendage follicle. Renamed follicle placode. Fixes [1266](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1266)
   * NT: suprapubic skin, fixes [1272](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1272)
   * Updated facial lymph node def
   * Removed equiv axiom for hyoid skeleton. Still need to determine correct DP. Fixes [1271](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1271)
 * admin
   * ceding 3 terms to uberon-insect... https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1262
   * Standardized spelling of Malpighian.
   * fixed koala typo
   * Removing many with the auto-generated comment
   * Removed evolved-from axioms, fixes [1270](https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/1270)
   * obsolete lobe. Fixes https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon-phenoscape-ext/issues/5

### New Class : [zonary placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036153)

 * [zonary placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036153) *[taxon notes](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBPROP_0000008)* characteristic of carnivores
 * [zonary placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036153) *[label](http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label)* zonary placenta
 * [zonary placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036153) **SubClassOf** [placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001987)
 * [zonary placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036153) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* A placenta in which the chorionic villi have aggregated to form a broad band that circles about the center of the chorion. Such zones may be complete circles (such as those in dogs and cats) or incomplete (such as those in bears and seals). It is thought that zonary placentae form from diffuse placentae in which the villi at the ends regress, leaving only those in the center to function. At the edges of the zonary placenta is the hemophagous organ, which is green. The color is due to the degradation of hemoglobin into bilivirdin. This green organ provides iron for the developing fetus. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[http://www.luckyhit.net/goats001.htm](http://www.luckyhit.net/goats001.htm) , [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[http://www.vivo.colostate.edu/hbooks/pathphys/reprod/placenta/structure.html](http://www.vivo.colostate.edu/hbooks/pathphys/reprod/placenta/structure.html) } 
 * [zonary placenta](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0036153) *[structure notes](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBPROP_0000010)* The placenta takes the form of a complete or incomplete band of tissue surrounding the fetus

### Changes for: [chorionic plate](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004027)

 * _Deleted_
    *  **-** [chorionic plate](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004027) *[definition](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115)* hat portion of the chorionic wall in the region of its uterine attachment, which gives rise to chorionic villi; it consists of the mesoderm that lines the chorionic vesicle and, on the maternal side, of the trophoblast that lines the intervillous spaces; in the last half of gestation, the mesodermal connective tissue is largely replaced by fibrinoid material, and the amnionic membrane is adherent to the fetal side of the plate. { [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=[http://www.medilexicon.com/medicaldictionary.php?t=69523](http://www.medilexicon.com/medicaldictionary.php?t=69523) , [database cross reference](http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref)=MP:0004560 }
